### Sign In Test Migrated to Playwright Component Testing

Source: https://github.com/microsoft/playwright/blob/main/docs/src/testing-library-js.md

Shows the migration of a sign-in test from Testing Library to Playwright's experimental component testing. It uses Playwright's `mount` fixture to render the component and leverages Playwright locators for interactions and assertions, replacing `userEvent` and `screen` queries.

```javascript
const { test, expect } = require('@playwright/experimental-ct-react');

test('sign in', async ({ mount }) => {
  // Setup the page.
  const component = await mount(<SignInPage />);

  // Perform actions.
  await component.getByLabel('Username').fill('John');
  await component.getByLabel('Password').fill('secret');
  await component.getByRole('button', { name: 'Sign in' }).click();

  // Verify signed in state by waiting until "Welcome" message appears.
  await expect(component.getByText('Welcome, John')).toBeVisible();
});
```

