### Example Component Test in JavaScript

Source: https://github.com/microsoft/playwright/blob/main/docs/src/test-components-js.md

Demonstrates a typical component test using Playwright. It shows how to mount a component, interact with it, and assert its state and behavior. This example uses a hypothetical Button component and checks for click events.

```javascript
test('event should work', async ({ mount }) => {
  let clicked = false;

  // Mount a component. Returns locator pointing to the component.
  const component = await mount(
    <Button title="Submit" onClick={() => { clicked = true }}></Button>
  );

  // As with any Playwright test, assert locator text.
  await expect(component).toContainText('Submit');

  // Perform locator click. This will trigger the event.
  await component.click();

  // Assert that respective events have been fired.
  expect(clicked).toBeTruthy();
});
```

